# Rule of Diary

After completing work on a user prompt, update the AI diary unless an exception below applies.

## When to add an entry

Add a new diary entry when the prompt requests a **new feature** or **new capability** not already covered by an existing entry in `AI_DIARY.md`.

1. Create `prompts/NNN-short-kebab-title.md` (next zero-padded number in sequence).
2. Fill in the prompt file using the template in `AI_DIARY.md`.
3. Add a dated line to **Entries** in `AI_DIARY.md` linking to that file.

Do this as part of the same task — do not leave it for the user to do later.

## When to skip

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| User says **skip diary**, **don't update diary**, or similar | Do not add an entry |
| Prompt **polishes** an existing feature (bug fix, tweak, refactor, styling, performance) already logged in the diary | Do not add a new entry |
| Question-only, explanation, or review with no code changes | Do not add an entry |

## Feature vs polish

**New feature** — add an entry:

- "Add a power-up system"
- "Implement high score with localStorage"
- "Add poisonous fish that drain HP"

**Polish** — skip a new entry:

- "Make the bomb explosion bigger"
- "Fix fish spawning off-screen"
- "Tweak shark swim speed"
- "Refactor collision into a helper"

When unsure, check `AI_DIARY.md` **Entries**: if the work extends an existing feature already listed there, treat it as polish and skip.

